member.summary:
Gets the token used to display the sprite of  in formatted scaleform text (i.e. the scaleform uses the game function `SET_FORMATTED_TEXT_WITH_ICONS`).


Example:

Blip myBlip = ...;

Game.DisplayHelp($"Go to ~{myBlip.GetIconToken()}~.");

Game.DisplayHelp($"Go to ~{HudColor.Red.GetName()}~~{myBlip.GetIconToken()}~~s~."); // with a different color

Sets the  of a text label.
If the text label already exists, its value gets overwritten;
otherwise, a new text label with the specified value is created.

Sets the  of a text label.
If the text label already exists, its value gets overwritten;
otherwise, a new text label with the specified value is create.

Removes the text label value previously set with  or .
If the text label was initially loaded from a .gxt2 file, its value is changed back to its original ;
otherwise, the text label is deleted.

