Creates a copy of this style with the specified properties changed. For each parameter, if it is null the copy keeps the value of the corresponding property of this style, otherwise, it uses the new value.
For creating your own styles, the recommended way is to derive them from a base , for example . With this method you only have to specify the properties you want to change using named arguments. The following snippet shows how to give the style a dark red color and a drop shadow.
TextStyle myStyle = TextStyle.Default.With(color: Color.FromArgb(120, 0, 0), dropShadow: true);
